k Watkins|Vindver|G. Thornton|Gwin|Jenks|[[Kenny G|Kenneth Bruce Gorelick]]|East|T. Thornton|Mosley}}\n| extra10 = {{hlist|West|Lopez|DrtWrk|Vindver|Timbaland|BoogzDaBeast{{ref|a|[a]}}|Bourne{{ref|a|[a]}}}}\n| length10 = 3:34\n\n| title11 = Jesus Is Lord\n| writer11 = {{hlist|West|Lopez|Miller|Claude L\u00e9veill\u00e9e{{ref|h|[h]}}|Vindver|Mosley}}\n| extra11 = {{hlist|West|Lopez|Miller|Vindver|Timbaland}}\n| length11 = 0:49\n}}\n\n'''Notes'''\n* {{sup|{{note|a|[a]}}}} signifies a co-producer\n* {{sup|{{note|b|[b]}}}} signifies an additional producer\n\n'''Sample credits'''<ref name=\"sample\">{{cite news|last1=Hore-Thorburn|first1=Isabelle|title=Here's Every Sample on Kanye West's 'Jesus Is King'|url=https://www.highsnobiety.com/p/kanye-west-jesus-is-king-samples/|accessdate=October 31, 2019|work=[[Highsnobiety]]|date=October 28, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191029134318/https://www.highsnobiety.com/p/kanye-west-jesus-is-king-samples/|archive-date=October 29, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* {{sup|{{note|c|[c]}}}} \"Selah\" contains a cover of \"Revelation 19:1\" from ''[[Jesus Is Born]]'', originally performed by the New Jerusalem Baptism Choir under the direction of Curtis Hayes and Jeffrey LaValley.<ref name=\"Selah\"/>\n* {{sup|{{note|d|[d]}}}} \"Follow God\" contains [[sampling (music)|samples]] of \"Can You Lose By Following God\", written by Johnny Frieson, Curtis Eubanks, and Calvin Eubanks, and performed by Whole Truth.\n* {{sup|{{note|e|[e]}}}} \"Closed on Sunday\" contains samples of \"Mart\u00edn Fierro\", written by {{ill|Chango Far\u00edas G\u00f3mez|es}} and performed by {{ill|Grupo Vocal Argentino|es}}.\n* \"On God\" contains samples of \"Lambo\", written and performed by YB; and \"[[Oh My God (A Tribe Called Quest song)|Oh My God]]\", written by [[Q-Tip (musician)|Jonathan Davis]], [[Ali Shaheed Muhammad]], [[Busta Rhymes|Trevor Smith]], and [[Phife Dawg|Malik Taylor]], and performed by [[A Tribe Called Quest]] featuring [[Busta Rhymes]].\n* {{sup|{{note|f|[f]}}}} \"Water\" contains an [[Interpolation (popular music)|interpolation]] of \"[[We're All Water]]\", written by [[Yoko Ono]] and performed by Ono and [[John Lennon]], and contains samples of \"Blow Job\", written and performed by [[Bruce Haack]].\n* {{sup|{{note|g|[g]}}}} \"God Is\" contains samples of \"God Is\", written by Robert Fryson and performed by [[James Cleveland]] and the [[Southern California Community Choir]].\n* \"Use This Gospel\" contains samples of \"[[I Can Talk|Costume Party]]\", written by [[Two Door Cinema Club|Alex Trimble, Kevin Baird, and Sam Halliday]] and performed by [[Two Door Cinema Club]].\n* {{sup|{{note|h|[h]}}}} \"Jesus Is Lord\" contains samples of \"Un Homme Dans La Nuit\", written by {{ill|Claude L\u00e9veill\u00e9e|fr}}.\n\n==Personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref name=\"Tidal\"/>\n\n'''Musicians'''\n{{div col}}\n* [[Sunday Service Choir]] \u2013 additional vocals {{small|(1, 2, 6, 7)}}\n* [[Ant Clemons]] \u2013 additional vocals {{small|(2, 7)}}\n* Bongo ByTheWay \u2013 additional vocals {{small|(2)}}\n* Bradford Lewis \u2013 guitar {{small|(6)}}\n* [[Labrinth]] \u2013\u00a0additional vocals {{small|(8)}}\n* [[Kenny G]] \u2013 saxophone {{small|(10)}}\n* Jesse McGinty \u2013 tuba {{small|(11)}}, trombone {{small|(11)}}, trumpet {{small|(11)}}, saxophone {{small|(11)}}, French horn {{small|(11)}}, euphonium {{small|(11)}}\n* Mike Cordone \u2013 trumpet {{small|(11)}}\n{{div col end}}\n'''Engineers'''\n{{div col}}\n* Josh Berg \u2013 recording {{small|(all tracks)}}\n* Josh Bales \u2013 recording {{small|(all tracks)}}\n* Shane Fitzgibbon \u2013 recording {{small|(1, 2, 6, 7)}}\n* Zack Djurich \u2013  recording {{small|(2, 6)}}\n* Jesse Ray Ernster \u2013 recording {{small|(2, 6)}}\n* Steven Felix \u2013  recording {{small|(2)}}\n* Randy Urbanski \u2013 recording {{small|(2\u201311)}}\n* Jamie Peters \u2013 recording {{small|(2, 6\u20139)}}\n* Andrew Drucker \u2013 recordin